  "text": "Proof. We are going to follow the arguments of [CITATION_1] Sec. 8] applied to the diagonal form F = x ℓ 1 + · · · + x ℓ ℓ . In [9, Prop. 8.1] we construct a set P F with positive density in the set of all primes p ≡ 1 (mod ℓ). By the Prime Number Theorem the product M T := p p of the primes p ∈ P F ∩ [1, T ] satisfies T ≪ log M T ≪ T . In [CITATION_2] Sec. 8.4] we prove that there exist two natural numbers m,",
